g=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#8E9173 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#8E9173 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Pippified Lizard King</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/7/01 9:48:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> I am posting this as information only.  It seems there is a new guild on Karana, Shattering Steel, that has the potential to throw a monkeyt wrench into all the large target rotations.  Shattering Steel is a splinter guild from Harbingers, and they have the strength to do large targets up to and including the Planes.<br>
<br>
From the information I have read, Shattering Steel (SS) is NOT joining the KGC.  Meaning they are not following the rotations and taking all large targets as FFA.  Several guilds and alliances including Harbingers and AoVB are not helping this guild in any fashion.  No ports, no rezzes..... the full cold shoulder treatment.  The KGC is considering banding together to alleviate this problem.<br>
<br>
Meaning, they are willing to &quot;toss aside&quot; the rotations for the moment and band together to take down the large targets before SS can.  The loot all goes to the guild/alliance that was up for the target.<br>
<br>
As I said, this is posted for informational purposes only.  I do not intend to sway you or your guild, but provide you with information.<br>
<br>
Shattering Steel's message forum can be found here:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/bshatteringsteel">pub79.ezboard.com/bshatteringsteel</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
A post by Shattering Steel can be found in the KGC public forum at:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://kgc.igz.net/ubb/Forum1/HTML/000164.html">kgc.igz.net/ubb/Forum1/HTML/000164.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And anyone with access to the KGC forums should read the threads entitled:<br>
&quot;Shattering Steel / POF Thurs&quot; started by Endaar Flashpoint<br>
&quot;We have a guild willfully ignoring KGC&quot; started by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst<br>
<br>
I hope that I have provided enough information for you to decide on your own. <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/7/01 11:35:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> Unless they're a lot larger than what I saw I wouldnt worry too much.  The only real large rotational targets they can concievably take out are Vox and Naggy, and that assumes they have enough lower level players for the rush, and enough high (55+) players to buff.  Other than that, they certainly cant take out Trak or the Gods and even Gore and Woushi would probably give them trouble.  The main reason is these larger targets are not a spur of the moment raid.  You saw how hard it was for CoG to muster strength on our previous Vox raid with less than 6 hours warning.  How many people do you think SS will be able to muster with only thier guild to call upon?  <br>
<br>
Some targets they can always camp I suppose, like VS.  But that gets boring after a longtime.  And of course if they try to jump your plane, just invoke PNP on them.  They will eventually get the message.<br>
<br>
It sounds to me as if they are just thinking that by ignoring KGC they can get the phat lewt faster.  In reality guilds abide by KGC because it is the best way we've found to go.  Large targets and Planes take a longtime to setup for, even for the experienced.  An hour is about the minimum I've seen for a Plane raid, and lets not go into how long it takes to clear to Trak.  When you add in PNP its simply not going to be worthwhile for them in the long run.  Even without being shunned.  The rotational system was partially developed to stop KSing and the anarachy of FFA, however, it also has the side benefit of saving a lot of time.  You just show up for your raid and go.  SS will have to camp for hours, perhaps days, if they want to KS a guild/alliance on rotation.  It wont be worth it since they are in the end only 1 guild and will have to compete against everyone in KGC.  It could be dicey for awhile but as long as everyone stays calm and mature about things, SS will eventually go away.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Crunchy!<br>
<br>
