</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A> at: 7/7/01 4:11:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/7/01 7:35:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> Well, it *IS* true that you can &quot;steal&quot; the plane from someone.  Especially a European or Asian guild.  However, if they try that my suggestion is for the other guild to go in anyway.  SS cannot have been in the plane for more than a couple of hours.  The farthest they could have gotten is about halfway.  At that point, thank them for breaking the plane and invoke PNP on them.  No one owns a plane or spawn, and Verant will enfore PNP.  The European or Asian guilds will probably have to start their raids a tad bit earlier now, or at least get preped in case, but thats about it.  Sure individually a guild/alliance can get screwed by them.  But think of the time investment in breaking into a plane, or even just staying through the repop.  SS does not have that kind of resources to screw everyone.  Because they are not operating against 1 guild or alliance, they are operating against over 18.  Add to this they are getting partially screwed everytime they do this and the generally shunning they may get and they will get their act together or disintegrate soon.<br>
<br>
What does this mean for CoG?  Not much I'd say.  Unless they are terminally stupid and pull the same thing on us.  In which case they will have managed to annoy about 3/4 of the server in one way or another.  One renegade guild will not be able to break KGC.  Not even Grey Hawk or Valoran could do that.  Its when several guilds decide that they dont want to play nice that you've got a problem.<br>
<br>
Just dont play their game by their rules.  Thats always a losing proposition.  Make them play by your rules.  They will discover for themselves KGC exists for a reason beyond greed and elitism.  they are only fooling themselves if they think they can get away with anything.  And in the end, this IS only a game.  Possessions, items, cash, these things can all be replaced.  Force them to waste real life time with no compensation and they'll shape up.  Believe me, they are not that hard core.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
