Seriously, that thread sounds more like some wannabe 14 year old who thinks that by posting that he can get some attention.  I mean, get real.  He states that many 60's are retiring out of boredom, but his guild will only consist of 58-60's?  Ummmm, sure.  Oh, and they have to have their epics.  Er...whatever.  Just how many epic wielding players do you know?  Thats what I thought.  Most of them belong to high level guilds and it took the entire guild/alliance/friends to get them their epics.  They are not just going to jump ship to screw all of their friends.  Whoever posted that really has no clue and just wants the attention his mother never gave him.  <br>
<br>
I've said it before and let me say it again.  KGC is not held together by trust, or friendship, or the feeling of being 3l33t D00ds.  Nor is it even held together because they all want the ph4t L3wt for themselves.  It is held together through mutual self interest.  A concept many others cannot seem to grasp, especially the poster of that thread.  None of the guilds in KGC NEED the rotation.  None of them, including CoG, have to abide by it.  They abide by it because the alternative is anarchy and rampant KSing.  It is a convenience, and that is a good thing in a game.  Before everyone gets excited about this, take a good look at all the level 58-60's with their epics on Karana.  Ask to inspect them.  Then go to Allakhzam's and look up their equipment.  Then ask yourself if those people really need to join an Uber guild who's sole purpose to to screw the guilds their currently in?  I mean, when was the last time you saw a level 60 with their epic that needed a BP from Trak?  They dont, if they dont have it (weird but possible) it'd pretty muuch only be a status item.  Believe me, that post is a troll.  Shattering Steel isnt, however, they do not have the strength to break KGC.  A few weeks of shunning and they will get the message.  Personally I hope all the members of SS have some reserve cash, because in a month they'll be petitioning Verant to move their characters to another server.<br>
