<br>
However, upon further reflection I realized something.  Shattering Steel has already taken a side.  They have chosen to do something the rest of us think is wrong.  And there must be consequences to those actions.  The rotation system that we know on Karana is pretty close to unique.  Most servers dont have one, and even the ones that do are restricted to mainly a few uber guilds.  KGC works for everyone.  Because of that I've decided to personally support whatever action the general community feels is warranted.  This does not include anything that would be against Verant policy rules of course like KSing or intentional training, even if Shattering Steel begins to adopt such methods.  I will not be dragged down to that level just for a game.  I do have reservations about shunning someone or a guild, but something has to be done and sitting on the fence or ignoring the situation is the same as helping SS.  I would urge anyone that attends CoG Plane or Dragon raids to also support KGC in this.  CoG can really only do Plane and Dragon raids because of KGC.  Without them, our setup times are too long to do this on our own.  I realize that many people may not want to take sides on something that does not directly concern them, but believe me when I say this does.  I do not believe that Shattering Steel is a major threat that can break KGC.  It is, however, a problem that needs to be dealt with.  I would further urge people not to attend raids that have members of Shattering Steel in them.  If they wish to stand apart from the rest of us, then they should stand alone.  <br>
<br>
This is not something I really wanted to do.  The major reason I dont have a guild is that I want to help those I can without worrying about politics and crap like that.  But this issue is larger than I am, and has the potential to become a server issue if ignored.  It probably wont ever be, and will die a painful death of its own, but everyone on the board is right to say that this wont happen if we ignore it.<br>
<br>
