<br>
I have asked my guild to support the ban on assistance to Shattering Steel members. That means members of my guild can choose not to SOW, rez, teleport, trade with or hunt with any member of Shattering Steel. My guildmates, as individuals with free will, can choose to ignore my request, it's completely up to them. I'd never tell them who they can be friends with or help. <br>
<br>
I have asked that of my guild, and I ask that of members of the Council of Guilds. I ask that you do not rez these guys, port, trade with, hunt with or buff members of this guild. This is not about loot, this is about peace. <br>
<br>
The KGC exists for mutual self-interest, in the name of peace. Rather than having to rush and scrabble to get enough people ready to kill Vox the moment she spawns, we usually have a good day or two of warning (sometimes weeks). We have a week to prepare for planes raids. The CoG is part of the KGC in that we adhere to their rules for planes raids and dragon rotations. The KGC isn't perfect by any means, but it DOES mean that guilds and people who adhere to the rotations get a shot at experiences they might have to wait a year for otherwise. Because of the KGC's rules, the CoG is allowed to let people who aren't even IN a guild, like Kellory, onto planes and dragon raids, WITHOUT joining a big uber guild. In short, the KGC allows the CoG to do something it couldn't do otherwise. <br>
<br>
I do not support the idea of &quot;beating&quot; the members of Shattering Steel to spawns however. All I am asking is passive resistance to the breaking of a community standard. Don't be mean about it, be respectful, and tell them why you won't sow or res them. Always be respectful, because these are human beings on the other side of the keyboard. But realize that as a community, the majority of players have adhered to and supported the KGC rules, including the people who have gone on CoG planes and dragon raids. For the interest of peace, I think this is one piece of passive resistance we need to enforce. <br>
<br>
As for the Uber Guild in formation, I can only laugh. <br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
The Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvelamon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velamon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/9/01 3:16:36 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.paralaxguild.com/images/velamon_sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Shattering steel issue</span><hr size=1> For once I agree totally with Haemish.<br>
<br>
Been in KGC, its affairs, its politics since its early days and I can vouch for its effectiveness and usefulness.   I am a rigid and stout supporter of KGC and the system we have built for Karana.<br>
<br>
There are wrong assumptions in many texts I see abound everywhere, ill try to post my feelings about this.<br>
<br>
KGC is not a forced stricture in the sence that it is a general assembly of leaders that choose to build something greater. KGC isnt a single guild or organisation, it is a community, a free going community that has built a functionning system for the benefit of everyone.<br>
<br>
As is, we have no rights to judge someone or an organisation that doesnt have the same beliefs we have or do not respect our organisation.<br>
<br>
As an organisation, we have two choices before us in my sence.<br>
<br>
1) Show Shattering Steel the error of their ways, show them the benefits of KGC for everyone over the FFA situation and try to live with them, of course without letting them disrupt our current organisation.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ( That is, if Shattering steel is a permanent fixture and not a Thrill of the month show for the benefit of a couple leaders ) </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  This should easily be done considering that KGC encompasses about 20 differents guilds that are functionning together.<br>
<br>
2) Ban Shattering steel completely and refuse them any help whatsoever, showing forcefully that KGC is a rigid organisation.  Organise multi-guild raids or events until the goals of Shattering steel are shown to be simply unattainable.  Mark its members as FFA and refuse them access / help in the future as a warning to others.<br>
<br>
Whatever choice KGC picks is actually up to us, Paralax will abide to the decision taken.<br>
