nocrasim aka Rushhex <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/11/01 3:10:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> The problem is that the leadership of Shattering Steel is creating this conflict. They are not interested in a friendly Karana. They are interested in filling their own item coffers without working with other people or cooperating with others. By contesting the rotations and scheduling that ALL planar capable guilds on the server have adhered to for almost 2 years, they are bucking a system that the majority of the community supports. Whether your friend knows or understands this, I don't know. It's not personal to him, or at least it shouldn't be. But as long as SS attempts this FFA stuff, their members will be treated in a manner fitting with the respect they have shown the rest of the server, which is nil respect. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujezelbelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jezelbelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/11/01 3:56:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> Bucking the system?   Hameish I am suprised at you.  Sweety, think about what you are saying.  This person came to the boards to tell you what happened to him in time of need.  I'm wondering, have you done that?  I really don't see positive thoughts from you much, just alot of neg stuff.  Please correct me if I'm wrong, I will not hesitate to say I'm sorry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/11/01 4:15:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shattering Steel</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry about your experience Rush, and to my knowlage that sort of behavior is not sanctioned in any form by any of the guilds supporting the boycott.  But no guild can really control the actions of another, and the only thing that can be done is for the guild leader to find the name of that individual and have a talk with them, perhaps even kicking them out of the guild if the offense is serious enough.  But people are people, not machines and their individual actions cannot be centrally controlled.<br>
<br>
And as individuals most of us have no problems with people in Shattering Steel.  The problem is that the guild has decided to declare war on the rest of the server.  You talk about the server splitting, I ask you who caused the split to happen?  Who was the ones who decided to stop respecting the time of the rest of the people who play on Karana?  As Haemish says, the rotation system is all about respect.  Perhaps this does not yet impact upon you.  Perhaps you are not high enough to take on the Dragons or Planes.  But one day you will be, and FFA will only hurt you.  And remember, Karana has a large Asian and European contingent.  Under and FFA scenario, most large rotational targets would be dead before most of us in the US even got off work after a server patch.  <br>
<br>
For the last 2 years the rotation system has kept Karana peaceful, it has served the common good and all the players on it.  Each guild and alliance respects the rights of the other and this respect transfers on down.  It is still in effect.  Do you really believe that Valoran or GH needs KGC?  FFA would suit their needs better.  They could care less for the most part since other than the occasional rotational large target KGC no longer affects them much.  The large Uber guilds have nothing to lose, and everything to gain under FFA.  But they support KGC because it helps the smaller guilds and gives them equal chances with the larger guilds.  You want to see what FFA is all about, go to almost any other server and ask 100 random 50+ players how they like Fear or Hate.  Unless they are in an large guild, they probably have never been there because they cant get in.  And by large I'm talking 100+ members mostly above 50.<br>
<br>
No matter how many good deeds individual members of SS may do, no matter how nice some of them may be, they are supporting a guild that is hurting the entire server.  From the level1 newbie who doesnt understand what all the shouts are about to the level60 who is getting trained in Fear because of the KSing going on.  It isnt about sides or a stupid guild tag.  Its about preserving a balance that has made Karana unique.  SS has brought the situation down on themselves, they have refused to talk to anyone about their position, and continue to try to cause trouble.  The real victims are people like you Rush who are caught in the middle, and the small and medium sized guilds and alliances that can lose access to the high level encounters in the game.  The losers if the server goes FFA arent some nameless faceless Uber entity out there.  The losers will be you Rush, me, Haemish, Zatriz, the newbie next to you, and all the lower level players who will not get to the Planes, or have the rush of getting the killing blow on Naggy.  It isnt about sides so much as respect and doing the right thing.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
